The paper deals with diagrammatic techniques for manipulating algebraic and co-algebraic structures, which are commonly used in quantum computing and quantum groups. This makes cs.QA (Quantum Algebra) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of !-graphs and !-box induction, which are techniques used in graph rewriting and combinatorics, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.GR (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also mentions the use of enriched tensor notation, which is relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
